The cell also contains a metal wash basin with running water and a metal commode.The entire crime scene was also diagramed to show the location of the victim and the white sheet.At approximately 0740 hours Judge James Lively pronounced the victim deceased and ordered an autopsy at the Dallas County Medical Examiners Office in Dallas
column14: Texas.  The body was tagged and placed in a body bag and released to Kenneth McAdams
column15: Riley Funeral for transport to the Dallas County Medical Examiners Office.At approximately 0800 hours Sergeant Kirkland obtained a complete copy of the Victims jail file record and began reviewing the file and attempting to contact the Next of Kin who was listed.  The next of Kin was Debra Barnes of Sussex
column16: VA who was the victims mother.At approximately 0810 hours Sergeant Kenneth Kirkland and Investigator Ronnie Ashmore conducted an interview with Jailer Verna Carr who provided a typed voluntary statement concerning the incident.  At 8:10 am oclock on this the 19th day of December of 2006 at the Hamilton County Sheriffs Office in the City of Hamilton
column19: Texas and prior to the making of this statement
column20: I was warned by Sgt. Kenneth A. Kirkland
column21: the person to whom this statement is made and who identified himself as a peace officer of the State of Texas.  I am 38 years of age.  My name is Verna Car. I am employed with the Hamilton County Sheriffs Department Jail Division.  I read
column22: write and understand English.  Sgt. Kenneth A. Kirkland typed this statement as I told it to him.  On 12/19/2006 I was assigned to work the 2400-0800 hours shift at the Hamilton County Sheriffs Department Jail Division.  At around 2400 hours I began my shift by doing a security check of the jail with Jailer Mark Flores who had worked the 1600-2400 shift.  We began checking Cell Block E
column23: Cell 28 and I observed inmates John Daniel Hanson
column29: sitting at the table in the day room.  Inmates Hanson and Bailey were talking and laughing.  Inmate Hanson talked with Mark for a few minutes.  Inmate Hanson asked Mark to give a picture of his son to a female inmate Amber Tellez
column30: W/F in Cell Sep 1.  Mark gave the picture to Amber.  Hanson was given two (2) Generic (Excedrin) Migraine pills for a headache.  Inmate Hanson showed no signs of being upset or depressed.  He was laughing and joking with Mark and myself.At around 2456 hours I conducted a security check of the jail and when I checked Cell Block E
column31: I observed Hanson and Bailey sitting at the table in the day room and they were talking.  There were no problems observed at this time.At around 0155 hours Inmate Hanson and Bailey were sitting at the table in the day room talking and laughing.  I did not see anything out of the ordinary.At around 0248 hours I conducted a security check of the jail and when I checked Cell Block E and observed Hanson standing in the doorway of his cell and Bailey was sitting at the table in the day room.At around 0342 hours I conducted a security check of the jail and when I checked Cell Block E and observed Hanson lying in his cell bunk.  I observed Bailey sitting at table in day room and he was writing a letter.At around 0439 hours I conducted a security check of the jail and when I checked Cell Block E
column32: I observed Hanson lying in his cell bunk.  Bailey was not in the day room anymore.At around 0515 hours
column33: I conducted a security check of the jail and when I checked Cell Block E
column34: I observed Hanson lying in his cell bunk. Bailey was not in they day room anymore.At around 0600 hours I began serving the breakfast meal.  I served breakfast to the north end cell block first.  I went to Cell Block E and looked through th door.  I opened the first cell block door and I observed Hanson to be hanging with something white around his neck.  The balls of Hansons feet were touching the floor and his toes were touching the floor.  Hansons arms appeared to be straight down by his side.  I went to the control room and began banging on the windows.  I told Anthony to call for Deputy Chris Cox
column35: 108 and get him to the jail now.  I was told by Anthony to stay in the control room and run dispatch.  I immediately dispatched Hamilton County EMS to the jail.  Anthony got his knife out and went to Cell Block E.  I then called Doris McFarliln
column39: and Sheriff Randy Murphree to report the incident.  I did not go back down to the Cell Block Area.I have read this entire statement consisting of 2-page(s)
column40: which bears my signature and I affirm that all the facts and statement contained herein are true and correct.  I further affirm that I knowingly
column41: intentionally and voluntarily waive the above rights prior to and during the making of this written statement.  This statement was completed at 0830 am on this the 19th day of December
column42: 2006.On 12/19/2006 at around 0915 hours Sergeant Kenneth Kirkland and Investigator Ronnie Ashmore conducted an interview with Anthony Burns who was the on duty dispatcher for the 2400-0800 shift at the Hamilton County Sheriffs Department.  Burns provided the following information for this report:On 12/18/2006 I was assigned to work the 2400-0800 hour shift as the 911 dispatcher for Hamilton County Sheriffs Department in the city of Hamilton
column44: in Hamilton county.  I received my shift briefing from Karen Kunkel who was the 911 dispatcher for the 1600-2400 hour shift.  During the shift Verna Carr who was working as a jailer conducted several jail security checks.  I do not know the exact number of checks that were done.At around 0610 hours Verna came running down the hall and was banging on the window stating that Hanson was hanging.  I went down the hall to the cellblock area and told Verna to operate the dispatch area.  Upon entering the E Block from the hallway entrance
column45: I noticed that inmate John Daniel Hanson was hanging from the day room entrance of his personal cell.  He had what appeared to be a sheet tied around his neck.  His feet were close to the ground
column46: but I am not sure if they were touching the floor.  Looking from the day room entrance to Hansons personal cell
column47: he was facing toward the left rear corner of the cell.  I did not notice any movement or hear any audible noises coming from inmate Hanson.  After unlocking the Cellblock door entrance
column48: I observed Howard Bailey standing in the day room by the table and he had a shocked look on his face.  I asked Bailey to help me.  Bailey held Hansons body up while I cut the sheet.  Bailey laid Hanson on the floor.  Bailey pulled a blanket off the cell bars from Hansons cell and placed it under his head.  Although I am not formally trained
column49: I tried to find a pulse on Hansons neck and wrist.  I felt no pulse.   I put my ear close to his check to check and see if Hanson was breathing and looked toward his head but did not see him breathe.  I noticed that Hansons tongue was swollen and loose
column50: his legs were blue and not a normal skin color.Hanson was cold to the touch.  I removed the noose from around Hansons neck.I secured the cell area where Hanson was lying.  I locked all the trustees down (in their cells) and placed Bailey in his cell.On December 19
column51: 2006 Texas Ranger Jesus Ramos took a voluntary statement from Howard Bailey

Any statement I make may be used as evidence against me in court;3.	I have the right to have a lawyer present to advise me prior to and during any questioning;4.	If I am unable to employ a lawyer
column60: I have the right to have a lawyer appointed to advise me prior to and during any questioning;5.	I have the right to terminate this interview at any time

column63: and voluntarily waive those rights set forth in this document and having knowingly
column64: intelligently and voluntarily make the following statement:I
column66: have been in jail at the Hamilton County Jail for Escape.  I am assigned to Cell Block E and I shared the common area with another inmate
column67: John Hansen.  I have shared this common area with John for approximately 2 months.  We have always gotten along with each other.  Our jail doors are not locked at night
column68: only the main jail door. Last night or early this morning myself and John was up visiting.  We were talking in the common area and I was also in his cell. We talked about several things and we sang songs.  John talked to his girlfriend
column69: Amy last night.  It must have been about 10 oclock.  They argued just like most couples.  I heard him questioning her about who was there with her.  John believed Amy was cheating on him and I recall him asking her why she was giggling.  He was very upset with her and commented to me that he was so upset that she made him sweat immediately.We talked a little bit about his anger towards her because he made the comment that if he ever got out
column70: he would kill the guy she was messing around with.  I tried to calm him down and advised him if she was doing that
column71: then it was real love.  He was also upset that he was going to be locked up for a year.He appeared to be depressed last night after talking to Amy.  I know a lot of his family was planning on visiting him for the Christmas holidays.  He talked about his bad relationship and he actually spoke of committing suicide
column72: which is hard to believe he would think like this because all he had was 9 months to serve.I dont believe he had a visitor last night after he got back from work.  He got back from work around 4 oclock just before shift change.I know he was having a hard time with being locked up
column73: always thinking about his girlfriend cheating on him.  He received a photo of his son and that bothered him that he was not part of his life.  I do feel he was emotionally upset and depressed.I remember when he got off the telephone from talking to Amy
column74: he did not talk about the phone call.  It took a little time before he became normal. I tried to convince him that she was not cheating on him because she would put money in his account and would come visit him.I remember after lying down for the night I sang him a song.  He asked me to sing him another song but I didnt.  I believe he even got up and came to my cell to check if I was sleeping.  I had my arm over my eyes so I never saw him but I believe he checked on me.  It was approximately 30 minutes after lying in bed that I heard a loud popping sound as if the bed sheets were stretching or ripping.  I didnt think at that time it was bed sheets ripping but I now know that had to be what was happening.I did not know he was thinking about suicide last night.  I thought everything was normal.I state that I have read this entire statement and declare that it is true and correct tot he best of my knowledge and recall.  I have not been promised anything nor threatened by anyone for this statement and have given it of my own free will.SUPPLEMENT REPORTOn December 19
column77: Ronnie Ashmore Investigator with the Hamilton County Sheriffs Department
column78: from the Jail.  Carr advised she had found John Hanson hanging in his cell.Upon arrival at the jail
column79: I made contact with Chief Deputy Johnny Slough who was in cellblock E with the body of John Daniel Hanson.  Hanson was laid out on the ground in white shorts and a pair of socks.  I looked at Hansons neck. He had what appeared to be a bed sheet tied around his neck.  Also around the door frame of his cell
column80: which is the first one in cellblock E
column81: there appeared to be a piece of sheet that had been tied.  Hanson had ligature marks around his neck
column82: and his tongue was slightly protruding and discolored.  Hanson had what appeared to be lividity setting in his legs.Sgt. Alan Kirkland arrived along with Justice of the Peace James Lively.  I began assisting Kirkland in processing the scene.  Chief Deputy Slough took photos.  Sgt. Kirkland and I began inventorying Hansons cell.  He had letters and pictures in his cell.  No suicide note was found in his cell.After inventory Sgt. Kirkland and I along with Chief Deputy Slough interviewed Verna Carr
column83: who was the jailer on duty and found Hanson in his cell
column84: as to the events of the morning.Texas Ranger Jesus Ramos arrived and he and Kirkland continued the interviews.  I contacted the Sussex County Sheriffs Department in Sussex
column87: who is listed as next of kin in the jail file.At around 4:30 pm Amy Mathis arrived at the Sheriffs office.  Mathis is identified as the girlfriend of John Hanson.  Mathis spoke with myself and Sgt. Kirkland but denied that she and Hanson had an argument over the phone the previous night.  Mathis also stated that John Hanson never accused her of cheating on him.SUPPLEMENTAL REPORTOn 12/19/2006
column88: Sergeant Kenneth Kirkland received a Cause of Death Report Case JP4179-06-2978LS for John Daniel Hanson
column90: Age 23 from the Southwester Institute of Forensic Sciences at Dallas
column94: Medical Examiner performed the autopsy on John Daniel Hanson.  Dr. Salzberger listed the cause of death as Hanging
column95: and the manner of death as Suicide.Based upon this Investigation and the information contained herein it is this Investigators opinion that the death of inmate Hanson was a suicide by hanging.  Evidence obtained during the investigation supported that no foul play was found to have occurred which would have resulted in Hansons death."
